    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but when historians talk about the \"rise of civilization,\" they usually focus on things like the industrial revolution or the development of European nation-states. does that mean those specific types of societies are the benchmark we use to measure how much a culture has actually progressed? like, do non-Western groups that don't follow that specific path get left out of the \"civilized\" category?",
